  "wikitext": "\n'''2-4-125\n\nAlternative term: Sector Screen (U.S.A.)\n\nAn opaque screen so placed as to provide a sharp cut-off to a beam in a sector light, and to reduce the angle of uncertainty (2-5-230).\n\n[[Image:Ch2_Fig38.jpg|400px|border]]\n\n\nNote: In French the term Cache is used when the device is located at the optic; and the term Ecran is used when the device is located at any other position, e.g. at the lantern or outside it.\n\n{{IALAFooter}}\n\n{{languages|Cut Screen (G.B.)}}\n[[Category:2.4 Equipment for Lights]]\n[[Category:Alphabetical Index]]\n[[Category:IALA Dictionary 1970-89 Edition]]\n[[Category:IALA Dictionary 2023 Revision]]"
